                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1042: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-17T09:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1919, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July 18, 5.25 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Railway manager informs me that Ecuadorean Government has remitted the 10,000
                    pounds mentioned in my July 14, 4 p.m., and that President of Ecuador informed
                    him yesterday that Ecuadorean Consul General in New York has been instructed to
                    remit 5,000 pounds additional.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
